@@ -0,0 +1,73 @@
+# Wave 8 adversarial review — `fix/wave8-shipping`
+
+## Per-bug assessment
+
+### Bug 1 — PARTIAL (`cancelShipment.ts:205-244`, `cancelShipment.ts:621-639`)
+
+The quantity restore itself now works for both full and partial LPs: it adds the snapshotted `shipped_qty` with PostgreSQL `numeric`, accepts either `shipped` or the snapshotted prior status, and the shipment row is locked before the LP rows. A second cancellation returns early while holding the shipment lock (`cancelShipment.ts:592-595`), so the action is idempotent under concurrent/repeated calls. The misleading unit-test expectation was corrected rather than deleted.
+
+However, cancellation still does not restore *from the immutable snapshot as its source of LP membership*. `lockShipmentLps` starts at the mutable, non-deleted `shipment_box_contents` CTE and only left-joins `shipped_license_plates` (`cancelShipment.ts:207-244`). Therefore an LP absent from current box contents is absent from the restore set even when it remains in the shipment snapshot. The snapshot controls quantity only for LPs that the mutable contents still expose. This violates the requested snapshot-authoritative reversal and can silently leave stock depleted while the shipment is cancelled.
+
+The new “DB-faithful” test does not exercise `cancelShipment`, the snapshot query, shipment locking, or repeated cancellation. It copies the final LP `UPDATE` into the test (`wave8-shipping-integrity.pg.test.ts:220-267`), so it cannot detect the defect above or prove action idempotency.
+
+### Bug 2 — FIXED (`ship-actions.ts:424-449`)
+
+The ship-time release now requires both `ia.sales_order_line_id = sbc.sales_order_line_id` and that the content line belongs to `sh.sales_order_id`. Every joined table is org-scoped. On a shared LP, SO-A's content can match only SO-A's line/allocation; SO-B's allocation cannot satisfy either line equality or the SO join. The real-Postgres SQL test demonstrates SO-A released and SO-B still allocated (`wave8-shipping-integrity.pg.test.ts:269-312`).
+
+The tightened join does not under-release a valid allocation produced by this flow: packing records the same `sales_order_line_id` that owns the allocation, and the shipment owns that line's SO. No allocation uniqueness migration was added.
+
+### Bug 3 — BROKEN (`so-actions.ts:303-310`, `so-actions.ts:735-743`; consumers below)
+
+Creation and allocation use SQL `numeric` pack-factor multiplication, incomplete/unsupported conversions return typed `unresolved_uom`, and entered quantity/UoM are retained in `ext_data`. Allocation and shipment contents operate in canonical inventory quantity. But not every `quantity_ordered` consumer was migrated, producing contradictory grains:
+
+1. **High — sales-order detail compares entered units with canonical units.** `fetchSalesOrder` aliases `ext_data.order_qty` to `quantity_ordered` while retaining canonical `quantity_allocated` (`so-actions.ts:303-310`). `mapLineRow` then calls `lineAllocationStatus(row.quantity_ordered, row.quantity_allocated)` (`so-actions.ts:245-255`). For 3 cases × 12, the UI model compares 3 to 36. Partial allocation is therefore reported as fully allocated as soon as canonical allocation reaches 3, and displayed `allocated_qty` has no matching UoM.
+
+2. **High — MRP mixes canonical `quantity_ordered` with entered UoM shipped quantities.** Open-SO demand groups and labels by `ext_data.order_uom`, converts shipped base quantity back into that entered UoM, but subtracts it from the now-canonical `sol.quantity_ordered` (`planning/_actions/mrp.ts:261-336`). For 3 cases × 12 with 12 each shipped, it calculates `36 - 1 = 35 cases`, rather than 24 each or 2 cases. It is worse for the newly retained literal `case`: the conversion recognizes only `box`, so shipped quantity becomes null and demand remains 36 labelled `case`. This is a direct planning overstatement introduced by changing the column's grain.
+
+The helper's arithmetic is PostgreSQL `numeric`; no JS float is used in production quantity conversion. The unit-test mock does use `Number`, but it is only a mock and does not establish exactness. BOL/box contents remain based on canonical packed quantities, which is appropriate, but the document/API model needs explicit entered and canonical fields instead of overloading `qty`/`allocated_qty` with different units.
+
+## Integrity and deployment checks
+
+- No migration is present, so there is no live auto-apply or existing-row uniqueness risk.
+- No new allocation uniqueness constraint was added.
+- No new `tenant_id` business-scope leakage was found in production code. (`tenant_id` appears only in test fixture setup for the platform tenant table.)
+- No new money/quantity float math was found in production paths.
+- The new `unresolved_uom` returns in create/allocate occur before the first mutation; no new `withOrgContext` return-after-write partial commit was found.
+- Cancellation's shipment row lock makes repeat cancellation idempotent, but its LP predicate is status-based rather than a version/checksum predicate and its snapshot-authoritative coverage is incomplete as described above.
+
+## Verification evidence
+
+`git diff origin/main..HEAD --stat -- . ':(exclude)_meta'`:
+
+```text
+.../shipping/_actions/__tests__/so-actions.test.ts | 116 +++++++-
+.../__tests__/wave8-shipping-integrity.pg.test.ts  | 330 +++++++++++++++++++++
+.../shipping/_actions/cancelShipment.test.ts       |   5 +-
+.../(modules)/shipping/_actions/cancelShipment.ts  |  17 +-
+.../shipping/_actions/ship-actions.test.ts         |  12 +
+.../(modules)/shipping/_actions/ship-actions.ts    |   8 +
+.../shipping/_actions/so-actions-types.ts          |  11 +-
+.../(modules)/shipping/_actions/so-actions.ts      |  89 ++++--
+apps/web/lib/shipping/order-line-uom.test.ts       |  22 ++
+apps/web/lib/shipping/order-line-uom.ts            | 148 +++++++++
+10 files changed, 720 insertions(+), 38 deletions(-)
+```
+
+Targeted Vitest raw stdout tail:
+
+```text
+ Test Files  4 passed (4)
+      Tests  75 passed (75)
+   Start at  10:48:12
+   Duration  215ms (transform 249ms, setup 0ms, import 376ms, tests 32ms, environment 0ms)
+```
+
+The PostgreSQL suite was not run because this review environment did not provide/confirm a test `DATABASE_URL`; its source was reviewed. Per project rules, no build or typecheck was run in the Codex lane.
+
+VERDICT: fail
+
+Required changes:
+
+1. Make `shipped_license_plates` the authoritative driving set for shipped cancellation (with a deliberate legacy fallback only when no snapshot exists), and add a real action-level PostgreSQL test covering full restore, partial restore, snapshot/content divergence, and repeat/concurrent cancellation idempotency.
+2. Keep entered and canonical quantities explicit in the sales-order read model; compute allocation status using canonical `quantity_ordered` and `quantity_allocated`, while displaying entered quantity/UoM separately or converting allocated quantity for display exactly.
+3. Update MRP open-SO demand to use one consistent grain. Prefer canonical `quantity_ordered - shipped base quantity` and label with canonical inventory UoM; alternatively use `ext_data.order_qty` and exact bidirectional conversion for every supported label (`case`, `carton`, `pack`, `pallet`, piece aliases). Add regression tests for partially shipped case and pallet orders.

